# Documentation Maintenance

- Keep `README.md` current when setup, core commands, project status, or documentation entry points change.
- Keep `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.cursor/rules/`, and `docs/ai/README.md` aligned without duplicating shared context.
- Preserve a clear distinction between implemented behavior and planned work for Silver, Gold, Airflow, Docker, Terraform, and analytics dashboards.
- Use `hpt ingest` for parsing docs. Record stale `hpt parse` references in `docs/cleanup.md` unless fixing them.
- Update `docs/configuration.md` when environment variables, defaults, or config precedence changes.
- Update `docs/architecture/` when pipeline boundaries, storage layout, or medallion responsibilities change.
- Update `docs/domain/` when CMS MRF schema handling, registry rules, or terminology changes.
- Treat ignored planning, notes, prompts, and research as non-authoritative working material.
- For unresolved implementation/doc drift, update `docs/cleanup.md` instead of burying the mismatch.
